items.text: Great food with totally affordable price! Try the angel hair pasta with minced pork. Portion is a bit small but tastes good. Chicken roulade is also not bad
Duck Rillette ($4) w/ fbaguette slices & salad. Duck Confit ($8.90). Angel Hair Pasta w/ Kombu & Sakura Ebi ($4), Red Wine Braised Beef w/ Mixed Green Salad & Potato Puree ($13.90) are recommended.
The food and service were good enough. Just a disadvantage: very crowded because of good taste :-)
Pistachio Creme is good, so is pan-seared seabass & beef tenderloin. Foie gras is not done to my liking though the sauce is good.
Presentation well done. Food tastes good too.
Duck confit is a must try here 👍🏻👍🏻
Duck confirm was good! Chocolate and hazelnut also great!
Nice duck and beef in a French style. Salad dressings are also good. Pastas parts was disappointing. Soup was dull. Very loud venue as sound bounces off every surface.
worth a try; Chicken Roulade altho the risotto base was so so only.
Confit de canard is pretty good. Pan fried fois gras though, was not quite there. Good value!
Луковый суп не вкусный, баранина - это несколько кусков жира в кислом соусе, утиная ножка пересушена настолько, что похожа на индейку. От французского ресторана тут только маленькие порции.
If you are a lone business traveller, get a dinner partner to come along. Else you'll be seated at an uncomfortable corner of the back of the restaurant. Not a pleasant experience
The duck confit was excellent
Too loud and noisy but duck and beef is good. Very soft and tender. Foie gras is good
По сингапурскими меркам цены средние.
Desserts are good
ダックコンフィがおいしい
Loud, small portions but good food and relatively cheap wine
Chicken roulade had no salt, duck confit was far too salty. Even for the reasonable prices, I'd say food here is still not worth the money and certainly not worth queuing for!
Mushroom soup is nice
The fish is yummy!! Must try...
The duck is good.
Good: foie gras, duck confit. Bad: monkfish, was salty and overdone. Very good: pistachio panna cotta.
No reservations taken but it's now only about a 25 min wait for a table on a Friday evening. Duck confit, cod, and beef were done superbly, so were the pasta, crab tart.
Try the confit of duck!! & Angel hair pasta w lumpfish caviar or sherry pork ! Yummmm
Garden salad is nice (yummy dressing)! So is their duck confit. Affordable, quality French cuisine.
Don't know what's the hype about this place. Food wasn't good/somewhat tasteless. First and last visit.
Lentils and foie gras. French onion soup not bad
Salmon entree was excellent , Cod main course was cooked well , but portion about half size of an appetiser . Duck good but sauce below standard . Dessert choice dreadful . No coffee served
Come after 8 on weekdays to avoid queues and have better service
•7/10 •Duck confit •Salted caramel lava cake
Food is tasty, but overpriced. Portions are too small.
Pistachio panna cotta is a must have!
The duck confit is scrumptious
Ordered a fizzy lemonade and all I got was a Sprite - service is not super attentive when busy... Steak was great as always though.
Good food, good wine, good desert...
The food is just OK, nothing special, the duck confit is too dry, while pasta is simply overrated. The dessert and special dishes tend to be better. Economical French that hard to appreciate.
Duck confit and angelhair pasta are good. The price is very affordable for the quality you get.
Excellent bang for your buck. Hard to find this level of quality dining in Singapore at this price. Food and desserts were both great.
Annoying and loud boyband music playing everytime I've been here. Spoils the ambience smh.
menu has expanded ... prices have gone up ... cute waiters are gone ... now they charge for water!!
Sublime, simple yet unpretentious french cuisine. Duck confit is a little dry but otherwise prepared tastefully. Skip the miniscule foie gras and order the panna cotta instead.
Duck confit is as good as it used to be in their previous restaurant in Joo Chiat!
Entrees n desserts r way better than the main courses!
Their menu is not extensive but they do sometimes offer special seasonal menus so go for that if u r adventurous and eat anything e.g. their mushroom tart (autumn offering) is delish!
Cookies and cream dessert is excellent. 5/5. Ice cream tart with cherries under a milk foam.
The pork belly ($10.9) isn't delicious or healthy.  Won't try this again.  Will get the Sea bass ($14.9) duck ($10.9), or beef cheeks ($24.9) next time.
foie gras is duck liver as described on menu. not to be mistaken for goose liver, therefore the price n taste difference

Try the duck confit and chicken with basmati rice. The chocolate mousse with hazelnut sauce is tasty. Service extremely fast and friendly. Come early b4 6pm on weekends, they do not take reservations.
Bring ear plugs!
Love the pork belly dish here! Crispy pork crackle, the meat is roasted till such tenderness.. I want more!!
Confit duck and duck pate is delicious. Price is reason for the serving portion. Definitely recommended!
Duck Confit and Saveur Pasta was too dry. Had a significant drop in standards since last year.
The pasta is sooooo good. Love it! They recently into a bigger portion of pasta for takeaway. Yet to try it though..
Excellent affordable French
JCBは使えません。VISAなら大丈夫です。
A little bit too salty for some of the dishes
Try their new dessert: Cookies & Milk! Unique presentation and utterly delicious!
Great service staffs!
The duck confit, pan seared sea bas, saveur pasta and saute potato are recommended.

2.20pm: Wanted dessert but server did not inform us of last order for lunch. Hence when we asked, kitchen is closed, no dessert. However, a table of 8 just came in and ordering now. What's up, Saveur?
The beef menu is tender and juicy, their potato gratin is delicious as well.
Must try the salmon confit of the starter!
Opens at 6pm but queues start forming at 530pm!
Very affordable french food! Don't leave the place without desserts :)
Cheap good food. A definite must try for everyone.
Small French dishes. Loud and slow.
Extremely disappointing experience; we have been waiting for 30 min and none of the army of waiters bothered to serve our order, although a table of 4 who arrived 10min after us got theirs. Bad.
Good value french restaurant
monkfish and barramundi quite value for money but desserts are better. for more, check out full review in the link url below :)
Food and presentation was nice; atmosphere not so nice. The chairs were grubby.
Nice ambience, delicious French food at affordable prices
Food in general is gd but music is too loud .
Guess for the price paid, customers do not have high expectations and are more forgiving. However having said that, the food is actually pretty average. Come for just an affordable casual meal.
Duck confiti was average, chicken roulade is bland. Not worth queueing for.
Love the pistachio panna cotta!
Good value. We always eat too much foie gras.
Bring the SALT! And try not to order the cement looking mushroom soup.
Food was tasty but presented badly, service was appalling but they comp'd my meal
Horrible service.
二年前に来たときはコーヒーや紅茶はランチメニューに無いって記憶があったけど、ちゃんとあるのね。デザートも選べるし。
They have the most gracious and patient servants work with their heart! Keep up the good work! The environment is simple yet comforting. Foods are no doubt nice!
Can't go wrong with the Duck Confit and Saveur Pasta.
great short ribs in wine albeit on the salty side.  good complimentary rocket and mushroom salad. can't say much for the garlicky potato gratin.
Affordable and delicious French food. Try the foie gras with lentils if you want it savoury, the one with apple if you want it sweet.
Servings are petite. It's like a kid's meal! BUT. The food is great! Can't go wrong with Duck Confit and Pistachio Panna Cotta. The Salmon Confit is excellent!
Decent food but horribly apathetic service staff.
Premium beef main course is fabulous please try
Pistachio pannacota is creamy, infused  with pistachio aroma,   minced pistachio in every mouthful, bring a surprise crunch to soft texture of pannacota.
Pistachio panna cotta.  Excellent end to a meal.
Why is everyone going gaga over the duck confit? I found it pretty average..
The serving is ridiculously small!! Especially for the chicken!!
